00145 /* Make sure enums are updated with thses */
00146 typedef enum PropertyFlag {
00147     /* editable means the property is editable in the user
00148      * interface, properties are editable by default except
00149      * for pointers and collections. */
00150     PROP_EDITABLE = 1<<0,
00151 
00152     /* this property is editable even if it is lib linked,
00153      * meaning it will get lost on reload, but it's useful
00154      * for editing. */
00155     PROP_LIB_EXCEPTION = 1<<16,
00156 
00157     /* animatable means the property can be driven by some
00158      * other input, be it animation curves, expressions, ..
00159      * properties are animatable by default except for pointers
00160      * and collections */
00161     PROP_ANIMATABLE = 1<<1,
00162 
00163     /* icon */
00164     PROP_ICONS_CONSECUTIVE = 1<<12,
00165 
00166     /* hidden in  the user interface */
00167     PROP_HIDDEN = 1<<19,
00168     /* do not write in presets */
00169     PROP_SKIP_SAVE = 1<<28,
00170 
00171     /* function paramater flags */
00172     PROP_REQUIRED = 1<<2,
00173     PROP_OUTPUT = 1<<3,
00174     PROP_RNAPTR = 1<<11,
00175     /* registering */
00176     PROP_REGISTER = 1<<4,
00177     PROP_REGISTER_OPTIONAL = (1<<4)|(1<<5),
00178 
00179     /* pointers */
00180     PROP_ID_REFCOUNT = 1<<6,
00181 
00182     /* disallow assigning a variable to its self, eg an object tracking its self
00183      * only apply this to types that are derived from an ID ()*/
00184     PROP_ID_SELF_CHECK = 1<<20,
00185     /* use for...
00186      * - pointers: in the UI and python so unsetting or setting to None won't work
00187      * - strings: so our internal generated get/length/set functions know to do NULL checks before access [#30865] */
00188     PROP_NEVER_NULL = 1<<18,
00189     /* currently only used for UI, this is similar to PROP_NEVER_NULL
00190      * except that the value may be NULL at times, used for ObData, where an Empty's will be NULL
00191      * but setting NULL on a mesh object is not possible. So, if its not NULL, setting NULL cant be done! */
00192     PROP_NEVER_UNLINK = 1<<25,
00193 
00194     /* flag contains multiple enums.
00195      * note: not to be confused with prop->enumbitflags
00196      * this exposes the flag as multiple options in python and the UI.
00197      *
00198      * note: these can't be animated so use with care.
00199      */
00200     PROP_ENUM_FLAG = 1<<21,
00201 
00202     /* need context for update function */
00203     PROP_CONTEXT_UPDATE = 1<<22,
00204     PROP_CONTEXT_PROPERTY_UPDATE = (1<<22)|(1<<27),
00205 
00206     /* Use for arrays or for any data that should not have a referene kept
00207      * most common case is functions that return arrays where the array */
00208     PROP_THICK_WRAP = 1<<23,
00209 
00210     /* Reject values outside limits, use for python api only so far
00211      * this is for use when silently clamping string length will give
00212      * bad behavior later. Could also enforce this for INT's and other types.
00213      * note: currently no support for function arguments or non utf8 paths (filepaths) */
00214     PROP_NEVER_CLAMP = 1<<26,
00215 
00216     /* internal flags */
00217     PROP_BUILTIN = 1<<7,
00218     PROP_EXPORT = 1<<8,
00219     PROP_RUNTIME = 1<<9,
00220     PROP_IDPROPERTY = 1<<10,
00221     PROP_RAW_ACCESS = 1<<13,
00222     PROP_RAW_ARRAY = 1<<14,
00223     PROP_FREE_POINTERS = 1<<15,
00224     PROP_DYNAMIC = 1<<17, /* for dynamic arrays, and retvals of type string */
00225     PROP_ENUM_NO_CONTEXT = 1<<24 /* for enum that shouldn't be contextual */
00226 } PropertyFlag;
